[ Apologies if you receive this email more than once ] CALL FOR PAPERS Fuzzy Logic and Soft Computing in Multimedia Information Systems November 5 , 1999 , 9 : 00 - 17 : 00 , Orlando , Florida , USA http : / / www . dat . ruc . dk / ~ hll / MM 99 fuzzy / home . htm 1 - day workshop in connection to 7 th ACM Multimedia Conference , October 30 - November 5 , 1999 , Orlando , Florida http : / / www . acm . org / sigs / sigmm / MM 99 / In the recent years much work has addressed the problem of enhancing database technology to better support today 's and future 's needs of efficient and effective storage and retrieval of multimedia information . The amount of multimedia information is rapidly increasing and made widely accessible through the internet . The utilization of information to its full potential requires powerful mechanisms for representing and processing information objects as well as knowledge about such objects . Examples of such processes and the kind of tasks using them are multimedia data analysis , object representation , object recognition , object classification , query answering , and information retrieval . The inherent vagueness and uncertainty in the object representation - as an image of the real thing , in the language in which we refer to the real ting , in the conceptual and spatio-temporal relationship between such objects , etc . - calls for the use of fuzzy sets and soft computing techniques . The aim of this workshop is to present and discuss newer approaches using fuzzy logic and soft computing in enhancing multimedia information systems to meet these needs . The topics of the workshop include , but are not limited to , the following as related to the theme and aim of the workshop : o multimedia information retrieval ( of text , image , video , and sound objects ) o content-based information retrieval o pattern recognition and matching in multimedia information access o image processing o similarity and soft computing in multimedia information access o soft computing and internet multimedia information access o soft computing supported information visualization , browsing and navigation o multimedia data analysis o classification and indexing of multimedia information objects o terminological knowledge and ontologies in multimedia object domains o fuzzy information & knowledge representation in multimedia databases and ontologies o ontology-based multimedia information access o ontology creation ( learning , discovery , engineering ) o enhancements of database technology for multimedia information objects WORKSHOP STRUCTURE The workshop contains a number of invited talks , presenting the results and positions of researchers and their laboratories . A panel will attempt to define the current and future challenges of fuzzy logic and soft computing in multimedia information systems . 09 : 00 - 11 : 00 Invited talks , each 30 min , including discussion 11 : 30 - 12 : 30 Short presentations of accepted papers from this call , each 15 min 13 : 30 - 15 : 00 Continuation of short presentations 15 : 30 - 17 : 00 Round table discussion , and summary of results Consult the workshop homepage for updates regarding the workshop schedule , and publication plans : http : / / www . dat . ruc . dk / ~ hll / MM 99 fuzzy / home . htm GUIDELINES FOR SUBMISSION The paper should not exceed 4000 words ( approximately 8 pages of text without figures at 12 - point font ) ; the body text should apply at least 10 - point and at most 12 - point typeface . The paper must be sent in PDF ( preferred ) , postscript , or Microsoft Word format , through email attachment .
